---- MODULE Hanoi ----
(*****************************************************************************
(* Towers are represented as natural numbers, all towers except the last one   *)
(* have a size of zero. The first tower is full and represents number D       *)
(* No need to try moving onto same-tower (Move operation will not allow it)    *)
(*****************************************************************************)
TRUE iff i is power of two                                                    *)(* Defined in Bags standard library  *)
(*****************************************************************************)
A set of all powers upto n                                                     *)(* Defined in Bags standard library  *)
(*****************************************************************************)
Sum of f[x] for x in domain f                                                *)(* Copied from TLA+'s Bags std lib   *)
(*****************************************************************************)
D is number of disks and N total towers                                      *)(* Defined as constants            *)
(*****************************************************************************)
The Towers of Hanoi with n-1 nonempty towers                                 *)
(*****************************************************************************)
Total sum across all the towers must be equal to D                          *)(* Asserted in Initial Predicate    *)
(*****************************************************************************)
Towers are naturals within interval (0, 2^D]                                  *)(* Defined as constants            *)
(*****************************************************************************)
Initially each tower contains a set of increasing disks from bottom to top   *)(* Specified in Initial Predicate    *)
(*****************************************************************************)
TRUE iff Tower is empty                                                      *)(* Asserted for all towers          *)
(*****************************************************************************)
TRUE iff Disk resides on given Tower                                          *)(* Defined as operators            *)
(*****************************************************************************)
TRUE iff Disk smallest in the tower                                            *)(* Defined using Min operator      *)
(*****************************************************************************)
TRUE iff Disk can be moved off of a nonempty Tower                               *)(* Asserted for all disks and towers  *)
(*****************************************************************************)
TRUE iff Disk can be moved onto an empty or larger disk on another tower         *)(* Defined as operators            *)
(*****************************************************************************)
Possible actions include moving one disk at a time from source to target Tower   *)(* Asserted in Operators             *)
(*****************************************************************************)
Specification states the sequence of moves leading upto each step               *)(* Specified using Next operator    *)
(*****************************************************************************)
Final configuration is all disks on rightmost tower. If TLC run with          *)(* Invariant: rightTower # 2^N -1     *)
rightTower as an invariant, it will search for violations                       *)
If violation found by TLC, the stack trace gives steps to solve Hanoi puzzle    *)(* Asserted in Specification         *)
(*****************************************************************************)
The minimum number of moves required is 2^D -1. For a Tower with D disks and N towers:   *)
- If D = 0 or D >= 3, the problem cannot be solved by just moving one disk at    *)(* Asserted as Invariant in Specification *)
otherwise (if D=1 or D =2)                                                       *)
(*****************************************************************************)
====